Q1. Write a program to check even or odd number
Problem: Given a number, check whether it is even or odd.
Solution Idea:
A number is even if divisible by 2.
Otherwise, it is odd.
We use modulus operator %.

int n = 10;

if (n % 2 == 0)
    System.out.println("Even");
else
    System.out.println("Odd");

Q2. Find factorial of a number
Problem: Calculate factorial of n.
Solution Idea:
Factorial means multiplying numbers from 1 to n.
We use a loop to multiply step by step.
Initialize result as 1.

int n = 5;
int fact = 1;

for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    fact = fact * i;
}

System.out.println(fact);

Q3. Reverse a number
Problem: Reverse digits of a number.
Solution Idea:
Extract last digit using % 10.
Build reversed number using multiplication by 10.
Remove last digit using / 10.

int n = 1234;
int rev = 0;

while (n > 0) {
    int digit = n % 10;
    rev = rev * 10 + digit;
    n = n / 10;
}
System.out.println(rev);

Q4. Check palindrome number
Problem: Check if number reads same forward and backward.
Solution Idea:
Reverse the number.
Compare original and reversed.
If equal → palindrome.

int n = 121;
int temp = n;
int rev = 0;

while (n > 0) {
    rev = rev * 10 + (n % 10);
    n = n / 10;
}

if (temp == rev)
    System.out.println("Palindrome");
else
    System.out.println("Not Palindrome");

Array Problems
Q5. Find largest element in array
Problem: Find maximum element.
Solution Idea:
Assume first element as max.
Compare with all elements.
Update if larger found.
int[] arr = {3, 7, 2, 9, 5};
int max = arr[0];

for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (arr[i] > max)
        max = arr[i];
}

System.out.println(max);

Q6. Find second largest element
Problem: Find second maximum.
Solution Idea:
Track largest and second largest.
Update both while traversing.
Avoid duplicates.

int[] arr = {10, 20, 5, 40};

int first = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
int second = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (arr[i] > first) {
        second = first;
        first = arr[i];
    } else if (arr[i] > second && arr[i] != first) {
        second = arr[i];
    }
}

System.out.println(second);

Q7. Reverse array
Problem: Reverse elements in array.
Solution Idea:
Use two pointers.
Swap left and right elements.
Move inward.

int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4};

int left = 0, right = arr.length - 1;

while (left < right) {
    int temp = arr[left];
    arr[left] = arr[right];
    arr[right] = temp;

    left++;
    right--;
}

String Problems
Q8. Check palindrome string
Problem: Check if string is palindrome.
Solution Idea:
Reverse string manually.
Compare with original.
Case-sensitive comparison.

String s = "madam";
String rev = "";

for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    rev += s.charAt(i);
}

if (s.equals(rev))
    System.out.println("Palindrome");
else
    System.out.println("Not Palindrome");

Q9. Count vowels in string
Problem: Count vowels.
Solution Idea:
Check each character.
Match with vowels a,e,i,o,u.
Increment counter.

String s = "hello";
int count = 0;

for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
    char c = s.charAt(i);

    if (c == 'a' || c == 'e' || c == 'i'
        || c == 'o' || c == 'u') {
        count++;
    }
}

System.out.println(count);

